quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  14,25,"It brings its crop every season (Literally: every while) by the permission of its Lord; and Allah strikes similitudes to mankind that possibly they would remind themselves"
  14,26,"And the similitude of a wicked word is as a wicked tree: uprooted from above the earth; in no way does it have any stability"
  14,27,"Allah makes the ones who have believed stand firm with the firm saying in the present life (Literally: the lowly life; i.e., the life of this world) and in the Hereafter; and Allah leads into error the unjust (ones), and Allah performs whatever He decides"
  14,28,Have you not regarded the ones who the favor of Allah with substituted disbelief and caused their people to inhabit the Residence of futility
  14,29,"Hell, wherein they are roasted; and miserable is the residence"
  14,30,"And they made up compeers to Allah, that they (might) lead (people) into error away from His way. Say, \"Enjoy (yourselves)! Surely then your Destiny will be to the Fire"
  14,31,"Say to My bondmen who have believed (that) they keep up the prayer and expend of what we have provided them, secretly and in public, even before a Day comes up wherein (there) will be neither selling nor fellowship"
  14,32,"Allah is He Who created the heavens and the earth and sent down from the heaven water; so He brought out with it (so many) products for your provision. And He subjected to you ships to run in the sea at His Command, and He subjected to you the rivers"
  14,33,"And He subjected to you the sun and the moon, both in a steadfast manner, and He subjected to you the night and the daytime"